NEWS GOV-MO: The University of Macau Awards Honorary Doctoral Degrees to Seven Outstanding Individuals
The University of Macau held the "2021 Honorary Degree and Higher Degree Conferral Ceremony" today (11th), and awarded the University of Macau's Honorary Doctoral Degrees to Professor Liu Zunyi, Professor Chen Kaixian, Professor Nakamura Shuji, Professor Li Lanjuan, Professor Li Xiaoliang, Professor Zhu Lilan, and Ms. Jiang Chaohui in recognition of their outstanding achievements and significant contributions to society and education.
At the conferral ceremony, the Secretary for Social and Cultural Affairs and the Representative of the University of Macau Governor, Secretary-General of Macao SAR government, Ouyang Yu, accompanied by Chairman of the University of Macau Council, Mr. Lam Kam Cheong and President of the University of Macau, Professor Song Yong Hua, awarded the Honorary Doctoral Degrees.
Professor Liu Zunyi received an Honorary Education Doctoral Degree, Professor Chen Kaixian received an Honorary Science Doctoral Degree, Professor Nakamura Shuji received an Honorary Science Doctoral Degree, Professor Li Lanjuan received an Honorary Science Doctoral Degree, Professor Li Xiaoliang received an Honorary Business and Management Doctoral Degree, Professor Zhu Lilan received an Honorary Science Doctoral Degree, and Ms. Jiang Chaohui received an Honorary Science Doctoral Degree.
In his speech, Secretary-General Ouyang Yu first expressed warm congratulations and high respects to the seven outstanding individuals who received the Honorary Doctoral Degrees. They have achieved extraordinary achievements in different fields and made outstanding contributions to the development of the country and the progress of the world. At the same time, Secretary-General Ouyang also expressed his sincerest wishes to the graduates and their parents and sincere respect to the dedicated teaching staff with a love for their job and academic excellence.
The professor of the lecture at the School of Humanities and Social Sciences of the University of Macau, Sun Yifeng, announced that Professor Liu Zunyi is a renowned economist worldwide, known for his outstanding academic achievements and forward-thinking education philosophy. 
In addition to his achievements in economic development, economic growth and the East Asian economy, he is also a visionary educational leader. 
In short, he has made outstanding contributions in many fields. 
Professor Sun Yifeng announced that Professor Nakamura Shuji is a pioneer in sustainable energy technology. 
He became one of the three winners of the 2014 Nobel Prize in Physics for inventing the blue LED.
Professor Nakamura's invention not only completely changed the lighting industry, but also led to the development of the white light-emitting diode that is widely used in daily life and industrial production today, making a huge contribution to human well-being.
Professor Sun Yi Feng read the praise of Professor Li Lanjuan and stated that Professor Li is a pioneer in the Chinese artificial liver industry and created a unique and effective Li artificial liver system. She achieved a major breakthrough in treating severe hepatitis and liver failure, significantly reducing the mortality rate.
During the fight against the COVID-19 pandemic, her team's "Four against Two Balance" program, along with the three technologies of artificial liver, microbiology, and stem cells, significantly improved the rate of treatment of critical patients.
Professor Sun Yi Feng read the praise of Professor Li Xiaoliang and stated that Professor Li laid the foundation for innovative research in operations management, shaped the thinking and practice of supply chain theory, and completely changed business models around the world. 
He is known for popularizing the concept of the Long Whip Effect in operations management and exploring measures to address this phenomenon.
Nowadays, in the face of the epidemic and tense economic situation, the whip effect is increasingly prominent, causing serious damage to the supply chain.
Li Xiaoliang's visionary research is like sending charcoal in the snow, helping the industry cope with difficulties and bringing huge social value.
Sun Yifeng read Zhu Lilan's praises and said that in her research work, she discovered a breakthrough and innovative staining technology for preparing samples, which enjoys a high reputation among domestic and foreign scientific peers.
She was honored with important titles such as fellow of the International Eurasian Academy of Sciences for her extraordinary scientific achievements and is entitled to a high position in the world's technological temple for her brilliant accomplishments.
Chen Xin, the acting dean of the Australia-China Institute of Medicine and Research, read the praise of Professor Chen Kaixian and said that Professor Chen has been engaged in drug research and development for more than 40 years, and his outstanding scientific achievements and important contributions to the country, Macau, the University of Macau, and the national key laboratory have earned him a high international status and reputation.
He fully embodies his sense of mission for contributing to the national development strategy of traditional Chinese medicine in Macau and the Greater Bay Area through his active promotion.
The president of the Macau University of Science and Technology, Mr. Xun Chengzhong, read the commendation speech of Mrs. Jiang Chaohui and said that the significant inventions and patents that Mrs. Jiang has participated in developing have accumulated more than 15 related to storage virtualization, navigation, file systems, and power management, all of which are highly practical and widely used, improving the convenience of human life.
As a successful inventor, Mrs. Jiang often simplifies complex science and theories for the general public.
Finally, Dr. Chen Kai read the farewell speech as the representative of the honorary doctor.
He was very pleased to see that the medicine industry in Macau and the Greater Bay Area has established a good example: from the establishment of the first national key laboratory for traditional Chinese medicine quality research at Macau University to the vigorous development of traditional Chinese medicine in the Greater Bay Area, Macau University has made a huge contribution by integrating excellent talents in the field of traditional Chinese medicine in the Greater Bay Area.
In addition, he believes that the management team at University of Macau has a foresight and insights, providing not only a scientific research environment for students but also producing many responsible talents for the society.
He feels honored to have the opportunity to exchange and cooperate with University of Macau, and sincerely congratulates the achievements that the university has made in recent years.